dashboard.instructions_body_0: To initiate real-time data streaming, commence by registering a new device and completing the requisite fields. Create or edit the specified .cpp file for the Arduino or any compatible platform, and subsequently, attach the pertinent files. Utilize a dedicated bridgeâ€”a computer running a script designed to read data from the serial port and transmit it to the server. Once all preparations are in place, activate the streaming process by clicking the "Activate" button within the "Stream" tab. For more detailed information, refer to the instructions below.
dashboard.instructions_body_1: Certain data, including the password, device ID, and serial port information, must be provided within the bridge script for establishing a connection to the Arduino board. The provided script facilitates the search for all available ports. Once found, replace the original code with the required COM port value.
dashboard.instructions_body_2: Certain data must be supplied in the bridge script, including the password, device ID, and serial port information for establishing a connection with the Arduino board. The provided code reads data from the serial port and transmits it to the server. Ensure that the password remains consistent.
